# Docker Rules for ML Services

## Critical Rules
- NEVER bake model artifacts into Docker images — use Init Container + `emptyDir` (D-11)
- ALWAYS use multi-stage builds: builder stage + slim runtime stage
- ALWAYS run as non-root user with explicit `USER` directive
- ALWAYS add `HEALTHCHECK` instruction
- `uvicorn --workers 1` in CMD — HPA handles scale (D-01)

## Correct Pattern
```dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim AS builder
WORKDIR /build
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --user --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

FROM python:3.11-slim
WORKDIR /app
RUN useradd --create-home appuser
COPY --from=builder /root/.local /home/appuser/.local
COPY app/ ./app/
USER appuser
HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=5s CMD curl -sf http://localhost:8000/health || exit 1
CMD ["uvicorn", "app.main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000", "--workers", "1"]
```

## Checklist
- [ ] Multi-stage build
- [ ] Non-root USER
- [ ] HEALTHCHECK
- [ ] `--workers 1` in CMD
- [ ] No model files in COPY
